# HeroUI Best Practices

- Use HeroUI as the default component layer; avoid mixing overlapping UI systems.
- Wrap repeated HeroUI compositions in local design-system components.
- Keep variant usage consistent with documented product design decisions.
- Prefer controlled components for form/state-heavy flows; avoid mixed control modes.
- Preserve accessibility defaults; do not remove labels, roles, or focus indicators.
- Use `className` overrides minimally; prefer theme tokens and supported variants first.
- Avoid deep one-off style overrides that make upgrades fragile.
- Centralize theme and provider configuration; keep it out of leaf components.
- Validate behavior across keyboard navigation, disabled states, loading, and errors.
